Defending champion  Spain  was tied
0-0 against  Portugal  after 20 minutes of the first half in their
semifinal match at soccerâ€™s European Championship.  The winner of the match at the Donbass Arena in Donetsk,
Ukraine will play record three-time winner Germany or Italy in
the July 1 final.  Spain, also the current world champion, is aiming to become
the first team to successfully defend the title. Portugal,
without a major title, was runner-up in 2004.  The other semifinal will be played tomorrow in Warsaw.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
